-- Bluebay Jumps 32% After It Agrees to Be Purchased by RBC for $1.5 Billion
-- B y   J a m e s   A m o t t
-- 2010-10-18T07:06:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/bluebay-jumps-32-after-it-agrees-to-be-purchased-by-rbc-for-1-5-billion.html
BlueBay Asset Management Plc shares
rose 32 percent after the company said it agreed to be bought by
Royal Bank of Canada for about 963 million pounds ($1.5
billion).  Bluebay stockholders will receive 485 pence in cash for
each share, the company said in a statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Amott at 
 jamott@bloomberg.net  